Anonymous Fri 18 Jun 2021 22:13:17 No.39528433 Report
Quoted By: >>39528677 >>39530589 >>39530647 >>39530671 >>39534743 >>39547255
>>39528083
Not him but I will say that getting into the mindset that anthros would just be perfect partners is dangerous levels of wish fulfillment. They'd also be people subject to conscious thoughts, social pressures, and other such things of advanced life in civilization along with their regular biological impulses. Besides, another issue of making them so idealistic is the issue that it makes humans seem horrible in comparison. In certain areas not with merit, sure, but doing so to such a degree raises the question: Why would anyone choose a human. Even in realistic scenarios where they follow a similar path to us and become more monogamous as they advanced there'd still be the issue of how humans would be viewed in comparison. After all, if anthros are universally less promiscuous than humans, that also means that humans would be the most promiscuous of the sapient species. When you look at it that way, it shifts from "we could have better partners" to "we would be shunned by everyone else". Because seriously, who would want to date someone who's vastly more likely to cheat on them, especially when they strongly value monogamy?
